Aujeszky's disease [pseudorabies], Finland
------------------------------------------
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 16 Oct 2021
Confirmed: 8 Nov 2021
Reported: 9 Nov 2021
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 22 Sep 2019
Causal agent: Aujeszky's disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location 1: Kitee, Middle Karelia, North Karelia, Eastern Finland
Started: 16 Oct 2021
Epidemiological unit: Not applicable
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Wild boar (_Sus scrofa_): Suidae-Artiodactyla / - / 1 / - / - / - / -
Affected population: A hunted wild boar was found positive for antibodies of Aujesky's disease.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: The outbreak does not affect the Aujeszky's disease free status of Finland, since it was found in a wild boar. The domestic population remains free of AujeszkyÂ´s disease. All domestic pigs kept outdoors in Finland are protected from contacts with wild boars by double-fencing.

Control measures
Control measures applied in domestic and wild: screening.

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Finnish Food Authority (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Wild boar / Real-time polymerase chain reaction (real-time PCR) / 29 Oct 2021 / Negative
Wild boar / Competitive enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay for antibody detection (Ab c-ELISA) / 29 Oct 2021 / Positive
Wild boar / Virus neutralisation tests (Ab VNT) / 8 Nov 2021 / Positive

